<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Foresee Planning</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.2.0/jquery.mobile-1.2.0.min.css" />
    <script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.8.2.min.js"></script>
    <script src="http://code.jquery.com/mobile/1.2.0/jquery.mobile-1.2.0.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
    <%- js("join") %>
    <style type="text/css">
        .card_holder {
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 20px;
        }

        .card {
            background-color: white;
            border: 4px solid #92746b;
            border-radius: 10px;
            margin: 10px;
            padding: 20px 0px 20px 0px;

            font-size: 30px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<input type="hidden" id="room" value="<%=@id%>"/>
<input type="hidden" id="socketUrl" value="<%=@socketUrl%>"/>
<!-- Start of first page: #one -->
<div data-role="page" id="p1">
    <div data-role="header">
        <h1>Join</h1>
    </div><!-- /header -->

    <div data-role="content" >
        <h2>Login</h2>

        <p>This is where participants enter their name to join the estimation session. They should not
            be required any kind of login but their names. For the real thing, we would need a duplicate name check</p>

        <div data-role="fieldcontain">
            <label for="name">Your Name:</label>
            <input type="text" name="name" id="name" value=""  />
        </div>
        <button id="add" type="button" data-theme="b">Join</button>
    </div><!-- /content -->

    <div data-role="footer">
        2012. Huskycode
    </div><!-- /footer -->
</div><!-- /page one -->

<div data-role="page" id="p2">
    <div data-role="header">
        <h1>Estimate</h1>
    </div><!-- /header -->

    <div data-role="content" >
        <h2>Story</h2>

        <p>The current story to estimate should appear here. And it should always in sync with what is being estimated
            by everybody.</p>

        <div data-role="fieldcontain">
            <label for="select-choice-1" class="select">Estimate:</label>
            <select name="select-choice-1" id="vote">
                <option value="1">1</option>
                <option value="2">2</option>
                <option value="3">3</option>
                <option value="5">5</option>
                <option value="8">8</option>
                <option value="13">13</option>
                <option value="20">20</option>
                <option value="40">40</option>
                <option value="60">60</option>
                <option value="100">100</option>
            </select>
            <button id="voteButton" type="button" data-theme="b">Vote</button>
        </div>

    </div><!-- /content -->


<div data-role="footer">
        &copy; Copyright 2012, Huskycode
    </div><!-- /footer -->
</div>

<div data-role="page" id="p3">
<div data-role="header">
    <h1>Vote Results</h1>
    <a id="voteResultBack" type="button" data-theme="b" href="#p2" data-transition="slide" data-direction="reverse">Back</a>
</div><!-- /header -->

<div data-role="content" >
</div><!-- /content -->
    <div id="cards" class="ui-grid-b">
        <div class="ui-block-a"><div class="card_holder"><div class="card">?</div>Name</div></div>
        <div class="ui-block-b"><div class="card_holder"><div class="card">?</div>Name</div></div>
        <div class="ui-block-c"><div class="card_holder"><div class="card">?</div>Name</div></div>
        <div class="ui-block-a"> <div class="card_holder"><div class="card">?</div>Name</div></div>
    </div>

    <div data-role="footer">
        &copy; Copyright 2012, Huskycode
    </div><!-- /footer -->
</div>



</body>
</html>
